# Data Platform Modernization

## Overview

This project demonstrates a modern enterprise data platform transformation from legacy on-premises and traditional data warehouse architectures to a scalable cloud-based Lakehouse platform.

The modernization strategy focuses on improving scalability, reducing operational overhead, accelerating analytics delivery, and enabling future AI and machine learning initiatives.

All examples use generalized architecture patterns and synthetic data models.

---

## Business Problem

Many organizations operate multiple disconnected systems:

* Legacy relational databases
* Operational applications
* Batch ETL processes
* Departmental reporting platforms
* Siloed data warehouses

These environments often suffer from:

* High maintenance costs
* Slow delivery of new features
* Limited scalability
* Inconsistent data definitions
* Complex integration requirements

Modernization provides a path toward a unified, cloud-native data platform.

